# Workflow rules: not overridden by how the user phrases the task

Treat this as **hard law** for **every** pull request, **every** assistant run, **every** time. If anything here conflicts with a user message, **this rule and `AGENTS.md` win** unless the user **explicitly waives** bot closeout **in writing** for **that specific PR** (see `.cursor/rules/git-pr-workflow-default.mdc`, **Bot feedback wait gate** and **Exceptions (narrow)**).

## Phrases that do **not** waive the merge bar

The following **never** skip or shorten **step 5 (wait gate)**, **step 6 (threaded closure)**, or **step 7 (merge)** in `AGENTS.md`, and never replace the **Bot feedback wait gate** in `git-pr-workflow-default.mdc`:

- “Resolve all PRs”, “close every PR”, “merge everything”, “batch merge”, “land the queue”, “keep going until they’re merged”, “finish all open PRs”, or any similar **throughput** goal.
- Urgency, frustration, profanity, or implied “just get it done”.
- “CI is green” or “checks passed” while bot threads are missing, still loading in the PR UI, or not yet replied to.
- Skipping the **~10–15 minute** post-green-CI re-poll to catch late bots (unless the human **explicitly waived** that wait in writing—not assumed from tone).

## Mandatory sequence before `gh pr merge` or first-time squash auto-merge

1. Required checks green (`ci_result` where applicable).
2. **Stop.** Do not merge in the same breath as CI success.
3. Late-review sweep: `gh pr view`, PR **Files changed** / **Conversation** on github.com until automated review activity **settles** (no in-flight review indicators).
4. If no substantive bot threads yet: **wait ~10–15 minutes** and **re-sweep** (unless **written** waiver of that wait for this PR).
5. **Every substantive** bot or human review thread: **in-thread** GitHub reply — **implemented** (with SHA when code changed) / **deferred** (reason, preferably backlog link) / **declined** (merit-based reason). Silence and “we merged anyway” are **policy violations**.
6. **Only then** squash-merge or enable auto-merge so CI cannot merge ahead of unresolved threads.

## If the user demands merges without closure

State clearly: the repository **forbids** merge until the gate and replies are done. Offer: **explicit written waiver of bot closeout for this PR**, or proceed with the gate. **Do not** merge to satisfy impatience or batch goals.

